On Friday the Western Cape High Court allowed for the possession, cultivation of dagga at home, for private use. JOHANNESBURG Lobby group the Fields of Green for All' says it welcomes the Western Cape High Court ruling legalising the private use of marijuana for adults.The court has allowed for the possession, cultivation of dagga at home, for private use.The group says it has been fighting for dagga to be legalised for over seven years now.The organisation s director Myrtle Clarke says, We are absolutely elated. It s turned out a lot better that we had ever hoped for. We have always expected the amazing people in the Western Cape to tick some boxes for us, and that s exactly what they have done. I think the country is in a very good mood today. LISTEN: 'Unbanning dagga products could improve medical research'(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)